      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): skip stored delivery context for delivery.mode=none sessions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Cron jobs with `delivery.mode=none` explicitly opt out of auto-announce delivery\n- When resolving delivery targets, the stored delivery context from `none`-mode cron sessions was still being used as a fallback delivery vehicle, bypassing the `delivery.mode=none` guard\n- This caused duplicate messages arriving via alternating channels — the intended session and an unrelated `none`-mode cron session\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Cron / Delivery\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/cron/isolated-agent/delivery-target.test.ts` → 54/54 passed (including new regression test)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/cron/isolated-agent/run.message-tool-policy.test.ts` → 51/51 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/cron/delivery.test.ts` → 18/18 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/cron/delivery-context.test.ts src/cron/delivery-plan.test.ts src/cron/delivery-preview.test.ts src/cron/service.jobs.test.ts` → 77/77 passed\n\n## Impact Assessment\n\n- **Scope**: `resolveDeliveryTarget` in `src/cron/isolated-agent/delivery-target.ts` — the central cron delivery target resolver\n- **Downstream**: The new `deliveryMode` parameter is optional (backward-compatible); existing callers that omit it preserve current behavior. Callers updated: `run.ts` (main delivery path), `delivery.ts` (resolveCronAnnounceDelivery)\n- **Edge cases**: When `deliveryMode` is undefined or not \"none\", behavior is unchanged. When \"none\", stored delivery context is skipped entirely\n- **Hard-coded values**: None introduced\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Skip stored delivery context resolution when `delivery.mode=none` so sessions that opted out of auto-announce are never selected as delivery vehicles.\n\n**Environment tested:** Node 22.x on Linux, openclaw upstream/main at 2ef0589b76.\n\n**Steps run after the patch:**\n\n```bash\ngit show HEAD:src/cron/isolated-agent/delivery-target.ts | grep -n -A3 \"deliveryModeNone\\|storedDeliveryContext\"\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\n155:  const deliveryModeNone = jobPayload.deliveryMode === \"none\";\n--\n175:  const storedDeliveryContext =\n176:    deliveryModeNone\n177-      ? undefined\n178-      : resolveCronStoredDeliveryContext({\n179-          cfg,\n180-          sessionKey: threadSessionKey,\n181-        });\n```\n\nBefore (no guard):\n```typescript\nconst storedDeliveryContext = resolveCronStoredDeliveryContext({\n    cfg,\n    sessionKey: threadSessionKey,\n});\n```\n\nAfter (guard active):\n```typescript\nconst deliveryModeNone = jobPayload.deliveryMode === \"none\";\nconst storedDeliveryContext =\n    deliveryModeNone\n      ? undefined\n      : resolveCronStoredDeliveryContext({\n          cfg,\n          sessionKey: threadSessionKey,\n        });\n```\n\n**Observed result:** When `deliveryMode === \"none\"`, `resolveCronStoredDeliveryContext` is never called — `storedDeliveryContext` is `undefined`. The delivery target resolution falls through to the thread/main session entry instead of using the stored (potentially stale) delivery context from a none-mode cron session. The regression test at `delivery-target.test.ts:1289` verifies `extractDeliveryInfo` is never called when `deliveryMode: \"none\"` is set.\n\n**Not tested:** Live cron fleet deployment with multiple concurrent `delivery.mode=none` cron jobs and a failing primary delivery path — requires a production-like OpenClaw Gateway deployment with multiple agents and cron sessions.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n- Root cause: `resolveDeliveryTarget` used `resolveCronStoredDeliveryContext` unconditionally, which extracts routable delivery context from a session key without checking whether the owning cron job has `delivery.mode=none`\n- Missing guardrail: No check existed between the stored delivery context extraction and the delivery.mode contract\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- Test: `src/cron/isolated-agent/delivery-target.test.ts` — `skips stored deliveryContext when delivery.mode=none...`\n- Scenario: Stored delivery context is available but `deliveryMode: \"none\"` is passed → verify `extractDeliveryInfo` is not called and result falls back to session store entry\n\nCloses #94164\n",
        "branch": "fix/94164-cron-delivery-retry-filter-none",
